.TH "rtnl_register_module" 9 "rtnl_register_module" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rtnl_register_module \- Register a rtnetlink message type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rtnl_register_module
.BI "(struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "int protocol "  ","
.BI "int msgtype "  ","
.BI "rtnl_doit_func doit "  ","
.BI "rtnl_dumpit_func dumpit "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "owner" 12
module registering the hook (THIS_MODULE)
.IP "protocol" 12
Protocol family or PF_UNSPEC
.IP "msgtype" 12
rtnetlink message type
.IP "doit" 12
Function pointer called for each request message
.IP "dumpit" 12
Function pointer called for each dump request (NLM_F_DUMP) message
.IP "flags" 12
rtnl_link_flags to modifiy behaviour of doit/dumpit functions
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Like rtnl_register, but for use by removable modules.
